=========================================================
HOW TO INSTALL VIM FROM SOURCE
=========================================================

* For a Debian-like Linux distribution like Ubuntu, type

sudo apt install libncurses5-dev libgnome2-dev libgnomeui-dev
libgtk2.0-dev libatk1.0-dev libbonoboui2-dev
libcairo2-dev libx11-dev libxpm-dev libxt-dev python-dev
python3-dev ruby-dev lua5.1 lua5.1-dev libperl-dev git

* Remove vim if you have it already (which is most likely...)
        sudo apt remove vim vim-runtime gvim
        sudo apt remove vim-tiny vim-common vim-gui-common vim-nox

        * Now configure and compile vim, for Ubuntu users, you can only use python2 or 3

        cd ~
        git clone https://github.com/vim/vim.git
        cd vim
        ./configure --with-features=huge
        --enable-multibyte
        --enable-python3interp=yes
        --with-python3-config-dir=/usr/lib/python3.5/config
        --prefix=/home/$USER/vimc

        sudo make
        sudo make install

        * Set vim as your default editor with update-alternatives
        sudo update-alternatives --install /usr/bin/editor editor /home/pauline/vimc/bin/vim 1
        sudo update-alternatives --set editor /home/pauline/vimc/bin/vim
        sudo update-alternatives --install /usr/bin/vi vi /home/pauline/vimc/bin/vim 1
        sudo update-alternatives --set vi /home/pauline/vimc/bin/vim

        =========================================================
        HOW TO INSTALL YOUCOMPLETEME
        =========================================================

        * Install dependencies
        sudo apt-get install build-essential cmake
        sudo apt-get install python-dev python3-dev

        * Get YouCompleteMe
        cd .vim_runtime/sources_forked/
        git clone https://github.com/Valloric/YouCompleteMe.git YouCompleteMe
        cd YouCompleteMe
        git submodule update --init --recursive

        * Install with C semantic support
        cd ~/path/YouCompleteMe
        ./install.py --clang-completer

        * Configuration
        cp .ycm_extra_conf.py in .vim_runtime and make sure it is being loaded by
        vim on startup

        let g:ycm_global_ycm_extra_conf = 'path/.vim_runtime/.ycm_extra_conf.py'

=========================================================
XTERM
=========================================================

add this code to your ~/.profile

if [ -e /usr/share/terminfo/x/xterm-256color ]; then                             
        export TERM='xterm-256color'                                             
else                                                                             
        export TERM='xterm-color'                                                
fi

